Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a #pot{} of salted water for the @potatoes{3}.

Chop the potatoes into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook until fork tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pot, off the heat.

Add a knob of @?butter{1%knob} and a splash of @?milk{} or @?water{}. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Cover to keep warm.

Trim the @courgette{1}, quarter lengthways and chop into 2cm chunks.

Lay @Irish chicken breast{320%grams} on #chopping board{}, place hand on top and carefully slice horizontally until 2cm remain (don't cut all the way through). Open it up like a book.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is due to vacuum packing used to keep it fresh and is normal. It will still be delicious once cooked!

To a #small bowl{}, add the @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet}, @breadcrumbs{1%pack} and @oil{2%tbsp} (double for 4p).

Season with salt and pepper and mix well to combine.

Pop the chicken breasts onto a lined #baking tray{} and season with salt and pepper.

Spoon the @mayo{2%sachets} over the top of each chicken breast.

Sprinkle over the breadcrumb mixture then press it down firmly with the back of a #spoon{}.

When the oven is hot, roast the chicken on the top shelf until cooked through and golden on top, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When ~{10%minutes} of cooking time remain, remove the tray from the oven and add the courgette.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with salt and pepper then toss to coat.

Return to the oven and roast until tender, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> TIP: Use a separate baking tray if necessary.

Pop the @hoisin sauce{2%sachets} and @sweet chilli sauce{2%sachets} into a small bowl.

Stir well to fully combine.

When everything is ready, place the golden chicken on top of a large helping of mashed potato.

Serve the courgettes alongside.

Spoon over as much sauce as you like.